{
  "analysis": "The previous encoder still failed: generated non-empty streams decode as token count -513 and decsim crashes. Two concrete bugs are identified: put_integer emitted the implicit leading 1 as an extra binary bit; the decoder reads gc()-1, so emitted normalization bytes must be low_byte+1. We need combine both fixes and test small streams against /app/decomp and decsim.",
  "plan": "Rewrite genseq.c with corrected put_integer: unary length = n-tmp-1 leading zeros, one at context tmp+1+unary+ctx*99, then emit exactly tmp lower bits at ctx*99. Normalization emits ((low>>24)&0xff)+1 and scales low and range by 255. Test 0 tokens, one literal 1, two literals, and a match, comparing /app/decomp and decsim diagnostics.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /app/genseq.c <<'C'
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>
static long low=0, range=1;
static int cc[2*200000];
static int radix=255;
static void norm(void){
  while(range<radix){
    putchar(((low>>24)&0xff)+1);
    low=(low&0xffffff)*radix;
    range*=radix;
  }
}
static void put_bit(int bit,int ctx){
  int *c=cc+ctx*2;
  long split=range*(c[0]+1)/(c[0]+c[1]+2);
  if(bit){ low+=split; range-=split; c[1]++; }
  else { range=split; c[0]++; }
  norm();
}
static void put_integer(int value,int tmp,int ctx){
  int ans=value+(1<<tmp), bits[64], n=0, t=ans;
  int i;
  while(t>0){bits[n++]=t&1;t>>=1;}
  int unary=n-tmp-1;
  ctx*=99;
  for(i=0;i<unary;i++) put_bit(0,tmp+1+i+ctx);
  put_bit(1,tmp+1+unary+ctx);
  tmp--;
  for(i=tmp-1;i>=0;i--) put_bit(bits[i],ctx);
}
static void finish(void){ while(range<radix){ putchar(((low>>24)&0xff)+1); low=(low&0xffffff)*radix; range*=radix; } }
static void lit(int v){ int sign=(v<0)?1:0; put_bit(0,1); put_bit(sign,8); put_integer(abs(v),4,9); }
static void match(int off,int len){ put_bit(1,1); put_integer(off-1,5,2); put_integer(len-1,2,3); }
int main(int argc,char**argv){
  int n=atoi(argv[1]);
  int i;
  put_integer(n,9,0);
  for(i=2;i<argc;i++){
    if(argv[i][0]=='m' && (i+2<argc)){ match(atoi(argv[i+1]),atoi(argv[i+2])); i+=2; }
    else { lit(atoi(argv[i])); }
  }
  finish();
  return 0;
}
